    {
      "content": "Performance and scaling testing: On-premises to on-premises",
      "pos": [
        607,
        666
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Microsoft Azure Site Recovery orchestrates and manages replication of your primary data center to a second location so that your data is backed up and recoverable in the case of planned and unplanned outages.",
      "pos": [
        668,
        876
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can backup up on-premises private clouds located on System Center Virtual Machine Manager (VMM) to another on-premises location, or to Microsoft Azure storage.",
      "pos": [
        877,
        1040
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To perform the replication, VMM uses Hyper-V Replica, a replication mechanism that is built into Hyper-V in Windows Server 2012 and Windows Server 2012 R2.",
      "pos": [
        1041,
        1196
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It provides asynchronous replication of Hyper-V virtual machines between two hosting servers.",
      "pos": [
        1197,
        1290
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Any server workload that can be virtualized in Hyper-V can be replicated.",
      "pos": [
        1291,
        1364
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Replication works over any ordinary IP-based network Hyper-V Replica works with standalone servers, failover clusters, or a mixture of both.",
      "pos": [
        1365,
        1505
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This topic discusses the testing of the performance impact of replication using Azure Site Recovery in an on-premises to on-premises deployment.",
      "pos": [
        1507,
        1651
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It provides detailed information about the parameters and configuration settings used in the test, shows the test deployment step, and provided detailed test results.",
