    },
    {
      "content": "The goal is to examine how Azure Site Recovery performs during steady state replication.",
      "pos": [
        1835,
        1923
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Steady state replication occurs when virtual machines have completed initial replication and are synchronizing delta changes.",
      "pos": [
        1924,
        2049
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It’s important to measure performance using steady state because it’s the state in which most virtual machines remain unless unexpected outages occur.",
